- Store data layer is responsibility for saving, persisting, or mapping and serialization the data provided by other layer such as service layer.
- The main point is that this layer decouples everything related to data storage and persistence from other classes and layers of the application
- Some typical set of classed in storage layer
    - Keychain
    - NSUserDefaults
    - File manager
    - AVFoundation to store or retrieve audio and video files to/from disk
    - Repository object: perform actually read/write to disk/database
    - NSManagedObject: persist domain model objects to CoreData
